descript.abstract: Elevation contours exist for Dakota County and are as current as the date of the aerial photography. Two foot contours exist for the urban areas of Dakota County, as well as for Nininger Township, for Lake Byllesby Regional Park and for Miesville Ravine Park Reserve. Ten foot contours exist for the rural areas of Dakota County except for Nininger Township, Lake Byllesby Regional Park and Miesville Ravine Park Reserve.
descript.purpose: Elevation Contours can be used for surface water modeling applications to delineate watersheds as well as determine direction and volume of water runoff. They can also be used to determine areas of the County that are susceptible to erosion. Used by the private sector for preliminary planning of developments.

timeperd.current: 1992-updates are ongoing. Areas of update are choosen based on building permits, last date flown and roadway construction.

idinfo.accconst: Licensed. contour data is available to anyone. Fees are charged according to the Dakota County GIS Data pricing policy. MetroGIS participants and the municipalities within Dakota County receive the data at no cost. Data can be delivered to municipalities on CDROM or via ftp. Data can be purchased by other entities with a minimum charge of $50. For current pricing information visit the digital data portion of the Dakota County Office of Geographic Information Systesm website. Http://www.co.dakota.mn.us/gis/data/digital_data.htm

procstep.procdesc: Contracted vendors used to stereo-digitize elevation 'spot' points and break lines to create an ASCII file. The Department of Survey and Land Information then processed this information to create an elevation coverage called Contour2. Contour2 tiles are merged and converted to a shapefile for network distribution.

procstep.procdesc: Aerial photography is acquired from vendor, aerotriangulation and data collection takes place in-house by the Office of Geographic Information Systems in Microstation, and is then processed to an an elevation coverage called Contour2. Contour2 tiles are merged and converted to a shapefile for network distribution.
